headline: AutoZone Q1 Misses Wall Street Marks, But CEO Sees Bright Road Ahead

Quarterly revenues of $4.28 billion (+2.1% year over year) missed the analyst consensus of $4.30 billion. AutoZone said the company’s same-store sales increased 0.4% (or 1.8% in constant currency), while domestic sales grew 0.3%.
